1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,779
Chapter number one, verses 24 and 25,

2
00:00:01,779 --> 00:00:04,139
will be the focus of our study this evening

3
00:00:04,139 --> 00:00:05,840
as we study the days of creation.

4
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,900
I believe that we are continually reminded

5
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:10,199
of God's power and God's wisdom.

6
00:00:10,199 --> 00:00:12,119
I am certainly thankful that we serve a God

7
00:00:12,119 --> 00:00:15,199
who is omnipotent, that he has all power,

8
00:00:15,199 --> 00:00:17,819
but in having all power, it's necessary also

9
00:00:17,819 --> 00:00:20,840
that he has all wisdom, and he is omniscient.

10
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:23,799
We're thankful for that, and we see the harmony

11
00:00:23,799 --> 00:00:26,639
of God's character even through creation

12
00:00:26,639 --> 00:00:29,819
as we understand the power and wisdom of God.

13
00:00:29,819 --> 00:00:32,540
We're reminded so often as we read the Genesis account

14
00:00:32,540 --> 00:00:34,779
in the first chapter, and then even as we study

15
00:00:34,779 --> 00:00:36,400
other portions of scripture that deal

16
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:40,099
with the creation account, how God said, and it was so.

17
00:00:40,099 --> 00:00:43,819
It's so powerful to see in this chapter

18
00:00:43,819 --> 00:00:47,400
how the Lord and the power of his word,

19
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:50,259
and what a blessing it is, and we, of course,

20
00:00:50,259 --> 00:00:53,459
have made note throughout our study of the book of Genesis,

21
00:00:53,459 --> 00:00:55,459
and still here in the first chapter,

22
00:00:55,459 --> 00:00:57,619
as we've looked at creation, we've made note

23
00:00:57,619 --> 00:01:01,340
of the word and that is used in this chapter,

24
00:01:01,340 --> 00:01:05,199
and it helps us understand the successive nature

25
00:01:05,199 --> 00:01:07,699
of the events that are recorded for us

26
00:01:07,699 --> 00:01:10,980
to help us understand that God created everything

27
00:01:10,980 --> 00:01:14,040
in six literal 24-hour days.

28
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,000
These were not ages or periods of time,

29
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,620
some undetermined length of time.

30
00:01:19,620 --> 00:01:23,419
These were six 24-hour days, literal days.

31
00:01:23,419 --> 00:01:26,019
We find that often he'll use that phraseology,

32
00:01:26,019 --> 00:01:28,779
the evening and the morning were the first day,

33
00:01:28,779 --> 00:01:30,260
the second day, so on and so forth,

34
00:01:30,260 --> 00:01:32,540
and so we understand through the text of scripture.

35
00:01:32,540 --> 00:01:35,139
It's also important to know that the Lord,

36
00:01:35,139 --> 00:01:37,260
as he would speak to his people,

37
00:01:37,260 --> 00:01:39,980
and as he would give them a pattern for their work week

38
00:01:39,980 --> 00:01:42,720
and establish the Sabbath for Israel,

39
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:45,059
you'd understand that he would refer back

40
00:01:45,059 --> 00:01:48,300
to the week of creation as being the example

41
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:51,980
that he speaks of because in six days he created all things,

42
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:55,819
but on day seven, he rested, and he used that pattern

43
00:01:56,620 --> 00:01:59,019
for the nation of Israel to understand

44
00:01:59,019 --> 00:02:02,260
that they too were to work for six days

45
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:04,620
and then rest on the seventh.

46
00:02:04,620 --> 00:02:08,399
As we look at the sixth day of creation this evening,

47
00:02:08,399 --> 00:02:10,460
we look at this passage of scripture,

48
00:02:10,460 --> 00:02:13,539
really just looking at verses 24 and 25 this evening

49
00:02:13,539 --> 00:02:15,940
because really there are two monumental things

50
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:18,339
that take place on day number six.

51
00:02:18,339 --> 00:02:21,220
The first creative action, activity, if you will,

52
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:23,339
that takes place on day number six

53
00:02:23,339 --> 00:02:25,660
is that of creating animal life,

54
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,339
life on earth proper.

55
00:02:28,339 --> 00:02:31,220
Those animals that are mentioned in verses 24 and 25,

56
00:02:31,220 --> 00:02:33,699
and we'll deal with that, land-based animals here

57
00:02:33,699 --> 00:02:36,660
in just a moment throughout the evening tonight.

58
00:02:36,660 --> 00:02:40,339
But the other monumental event that took place

59
00:02:40,339 --> 00:02:43,300
on day number six was that God created man

60
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:45,860
and the crown of his creation,

61
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:49,440
and we will spend at least an entire service

62
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:52,380
dealing with that aspect of the sixth day.

63
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:55,020
In fact, we could look at just the statements

64
00:02:55,059 --> 00:02:59,539
that are mentioned in the account of how God made man,

65
00:02:59,539 --> 00:03:01,820
and we could spend a number of weeks

66
00:03:01,820 --> 00:03:04,300
just in those few verses of scripture

67
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:06,660
and deal with so many of the issues

68
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,899
that we face in our society today

69
00:03:08,899 --> 00:03:11,179
and how they're answered very simply

70
00:03:11,179 --> 00:03:13,699
by understanding what God told us

71
00:03:13,699 --> 00:03:16,259
in the very first chapter of his book.

72
00:03:16,259 --> 00:03:19,940
And it's amazing how that we have thrown it out

73
00:03:19,940 --> 00:03:21,740
as a society, as a culture,

74
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:24,080
and we have found ourselves in a mess

75
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:27,039
where people just can't seem to answer questions

76
00:03:27,039 --> 00:03:29,240
that are so obvious, blatantly obvious,

77
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,000
and God's given us the record.

78
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:35,259
And so we'll spend at least an entire message next week

79
00:03:35,259 --> 00:03:38,960
on that second activity that took place there

80
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:41,119
during the sixth day of creation.

81
00:03:41,119 --> 00:03:43,880
So our focus here will be on the land-based animals.

82
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:46,639
It's interesting, even before we get into verses 24 and 25,

83
00:03:46,639 --> 00:03:49,240
just to kind of rehearse, recap, if you will,

84
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:51,639
it's been a few weeks since we've been

85
00:03:51,639 --> 00:03:54,919
in the book of Genesis and studying the days of creation.

86
00:03:54,919 --> 00:03:57,440
We remember that on day number one there,

87
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,800
as it's recorded in verses one through five,

88
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,800
that God said, let there be light, and there was light.

89
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,240
We find that that was the energy

90
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:06,160
that God created in the beginning there.

91
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,479
And we find that on day number two,

92
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:09,559
he caused the firmament to be made.

93
00:04:09,559 --> 00:04:10,960
And it says that he made the firmament,

94
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,720
divided the waters which were under the firmament

95
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:15,199
from the waters which are above the firmament, it was so.

96
00:04:15,199 --> 00:04:17,320
And that was done on day number two,

97
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,359
according to verses six through eight.

98
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:21,519
As we continue looking through the days of creation,

99
00:04:22,399 --> 00:04:23,480
we find that on day number three,

100
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:27,839
that God had formed the sea, the dry land, and plant life.

101
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:30,359
And we find that then on day number four,

102
00:04:30,359 --> 00:04:32,559
the sun, the moon, and the stars.

103
00:04:32,559 --> 00:04:34,359
And I know I enjoy saying this

104
00:04:34,359 --> 00:04:35,959
because it's just powerful to me,

105
00:04:35,959 --> 00:04:39,000
how that on verse number 16, the last five verses,

106
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:43,320
it simply says this, he made the stars also.

107
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:46,760
And there are billions and billions of stars,

108
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,839
and he simply records it as saying,

109
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:51,799
he made the stars also.

110
00:04:51,799 --> 00:04:52,640
Isn't that amazing?

111
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:54,480
I mean, our God is so wonderful.

112
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,000
He transcends us.

113
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,079
We find that that's what we did on day number four.

114
00:04:58,079 --> 00:05:00,440
Day number five, sea life and fowls,

115
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:03,119
as we studied in our last lesson,

116
00:05:03,119 --> 00:05:06,480
and we understand how that he created those.

117
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,920
And then today, of course, getting into day number six,

118
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:11,559
land-based animals, and then as he made man.

119
00:05:11,559 --> 00:05:13,079
But it's interesting as we think about the fact

120
00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:16,540
that our God is a God of order and a God of plan.

121
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:19,899
We find that he formed the sea on day number three,

122
00:05:19,899 --> 00:05:21,179
but then it was on day number five

123
00:05:21,179 --> 00:05:22,700
that he filled it with life.

124
00:05:23,619 --> 00:05:26,220
We find, again, that on day number two,

125
00:05:26,220 --> 00:05:27,540
when he separated the firmament,

126
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:29,059
of course, the heavens from the heaven,

127
00:05:29,059 --> 00:05:31,540
and so on and so forth, the waters were separated,

128
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:33,540
that he made the sky there,

129
00:05:33,540 --> 00:05:35,980
as we would call it, as one of the heavens.

130
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:38,220
And we find that then he would fill it with life

131
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:39,739
on day number five.

132
00:05:39,739 --> 00:05:42,619
And then we find that it was there on day number three

133
00:05:42,619 --> 00:05:45,899
that he formed the dry land,

134
00:05:45,899 --> 00:05:49,019
and it was there that the dry land appeared,

135
00:05:49,019 --> 00:05:51,220
according to verses nine and 10.

136
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:53,619
And then on verses 11 and 12,

137
00:05:53,619 --> 00:05:56,059
it talks about how there on day number three,

138
00:05:56,059 --> 00:05:58,100
he brought forth vegetation.

139
00:05:58,100 --> 00:05:59,940
Now that vegetation that was brought forth,

140
00:05:59,940 --> 00:06:02,260
as we find here in the text of scripture,

141
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:05,420
is that that was the food source

142
00:06:05,420 --> 00:06:07,500
for that which he would later create.

143
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:12,019
We find that he mentions that at the end of the chapter,

144
00:06:12,019 --> 00:06:13,019
in verse number 30, it says,

145
00:06:13,019 --> 00:06:14,260
unto every beast of the earth,

146
00:06:14,260 --> 00:06:15,339
and every fowl of the air,

147
00:06:15,339 --> 00:06:17,540
and to everything that creepeth upon the earth,

148
00:06:17,540 --> 00:06:19,140
wherein there is life,

149
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:22,660
I have given every green herb for meat.

150
00:06:22,660 --> 00:06:23,940
And it was so.

151
00:06:23,940 --> 00:06:26,339
And then on day six, as we begin our study here,

152
00:06:26,339 --> 00:06:29,019
we find that he made the land animals.

153
00:06:29,019 --> 00:06:31,380
And so you see the order of our God,

154
00:06:31,380 --> 00:06:33,779
how that as he's creating,

155
00:06:33,779 --> 00:06:35,980
as we go through the chapter,

156
00:06:35,980 --> 00:06:39,420
how that each aspect of the creation,

157
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:43,100
it's sustaining that would be created next.

158
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:45,500
And how powerful that is for us to understand.

159
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:47,220
In first Corinthians 14 and 40,

160
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:50,420
the Bible says let all things be done decently and in order.

161
00:06:50,420 --> 00:06:53,739
And we understand that our God is a God of order,

162
00:06:53,739 --> 00:06:57,619
even as we find here in the Genesis record of creation.

163
00:06:57,619 --> 00:06:59,100
Verse 24, the Bible says this,

164
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:03,260
and God said, let the earth bring forth

165
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:05,019
the living creature after his kind,

166
00:07:05,019 --> 00:07:08,179
cattle and creeping thing and beast of the earth

167
00:07:08,179 --> 00:07:10,980
after his kind, and it was so.

168
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:13,779
And God made the beast of the earth after his kind

169
00:07:13,779 --> 00:07:15,220
and cattle after their kind

170
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:19,059
and everything that creepeth upon the earth after his kind.

171
00:07:19,059 --> 00:07:21,980
And God saw that it was good.

172
00:07:21,980 --> 00:07:24,059
I'm reminded of a verse that we've referenced

173
00:07:24,059 --> 00:07:28,200
on a number of occasion, Psalm 104, verses 24 and 25,

174
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,420
where the psalmist declares,

175
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:33,459
O Lord, how manifold are thy works!

176
00:07:33,459 --> 00:07:37,500
In wisdom hast thou made them all.

177
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:40,779
The earth is full of thy riches.

178
00:07:41,579 --> 00:07:43,540
So is this great and wide sea.

179
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:45,980
We're in our things creeping, innumerable,

180
00:07:45,980 --> 00:07:48,619
both small and great beast.

181
00:07:48,619 --> 00:07:50,019
And of course, we're reminded

182
00:07:50,019 --> 00:07:51,500
of several other passages of scripture.

183
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,459
Psalm 19, the Bible speaks about,

184
00:07:53,459 --> 00:07:55,299
the heavens declare the glory of God.

185
00:07:55,299 --> 00:07:57,380
The firmament showeth forth his handiwork.

186
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:59,880
What a blessing it is to see here

187
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,640
how that God is revealing, once again,

188
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:03,380
his power and his wisdom.

189
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:06,059
Notice with me, first of all, the declaration, if you will.

190
00:08:06,059 --> 00:08:07,640
In verse number 24, once again,

191
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:09,859
we see that oft-repeated phrase

192
00:08:09,859 --> 00:08:11,500
throughout Genesis chapter number one,

193
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,459
where the Bible begins and simply says,

194
00:08:13,459 --> 00:08:15,779
and God said.

195
00:08:15,779 --> 00:08:18,739
We find that the power of his word, once again,

196
00:08:18,739 --> 00:08:22,059
is evident here in the text of scripture.

197
00:08:22,059 --> 00:08:24,239
And you notice that the Bible says,

198
00:08:24,239 --> 00:08:27,779
and God said, let the earth bring forth

199
00:08:27,779 --> 00:08:30,200
the living creature after his kind.

200
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:33,380
And so we find that God, he's created the earth.

201
00:08:33,380 --> 00:08:36,000
We find in previous days of creation,

202
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:39,960
we've just rehearsed them and reviewed them.

203
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:43,359
And we understand that now, as he stands there,

204
00:08:43,359 --> 00:08:45,840
as God is creating there in this first week,

205
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:49,200
he says, he speaks, and we see the power, again,

206
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,760
of his word in Psalm 33.

207
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:54,179
The Bible tells us there in verses six through nine,

208
00:08:54,179 --> 00:08:56,479
a powerful passage of scripture.

209
00:08:56,479 --> 00:08:59,679
And the psalmist declares, he spake and it was done.

210
00:08:59,679 --> 00:09:03,719
The complete context of the quote there in Psalm 33,

211
00:09:03,719 --> 00:09:06,640
in verse number six, it says, by the word of the Lord

212
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:09,599
were the heavens made, and all the host of them

213
00:09:09,599 --> 00:09:11,359
by the breath of his mouth.

214
00:09:11,359 --> 00:09:14,320
He gathered the waters of the sea together as in heap.

215
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:17,200
He layeth up the depth in storehouses.

216
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,640
Let all the earth fear the Lord.

217
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:22,640
Let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him,

218
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:24,799
for he spake and it was done.

219
00:09:24,799 --> 00:09:28,479
He commanded and it stood fast.

220
00:09:28,479 --> 00:09:31,320
I think about the ministry of the Lord Jesus Christ,

221
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,960
and I think about the time in which

222
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,359
he's walking upon the earth,

223
00:09:34,359 --> 00:09:38,159
and we see that he would reveal his power to his disciples,

224
00:09:38,159 --> 00:09:41,520
and to obviously many of those within the land of Israel

225
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:44,440
during his life and ministry here upon earth.

226
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:47,119
And often through the study of the miracles,

227
00:09:47,119 --> 00:09:49,679
you would find that the Lord Jesus Christ

228
00:09:49,679 --> 00:09:51,820
was revealing his power,

229
00:09:51,820 --> 00:09:54,760
and how often he would reveal his power

230
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:57,280
with just a spoken word.

231
00:09:58,359 --> 00:09:59,840
Amen?

232
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,679
He does.

233
00:10:00,679 --> 00:10:05,639
just simply say it. He just simply speak it. And as he would speak it, as he would

234
00:10:05,639 --> 00:10:11,219
speak the words, you would see the power. I'm reminded there even as we look at

235
00:10:11,219 --> 00:10:15,079
the creation and we find how that God would speak to His creation and His

236
00:10:15,079 --> 00:10:20,039
creation always obeys the Creator. The only part of creation that does not

237
00:10:20,039 --> 00:10:26,959
always obey the Creator is man. And we find that here God reminds us of the

238
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:31,799
power of His Word. This phrase is used throughout the passage of Scripture,

239
00:10:31,799 --> 00:10:39,279
and God said. He spake and it was done. He said, let the earth bring forth. Notice

240
00:10:39,279 --> 00:10:44,359
in verse 24, He says, let the earth bring forth the living creature after His kind,

241
00:10:44,359 --> 00:10:50,719
cattle and creeping thing, and beast of the earth after His kind. And it was so.

242
00:10:50,959 --> 00:10:57,119
We find that in verse number 25 that the Bible then says, and God made. He made the

243
00:10:57,119 --> 00:11:00,639
beast of the earth after His kind and cattle after their kind and everything

244
00:11:00,639 --> 00:11:06,439
that creepeth on the earth after His kind and God saw that it was good. As we'd

245
00:11:06,439 --> 00:11:10,159
understand the context and what the Lord is dealing with as He's revealing to us

246
00:11:10,159 --> 00:11:15,199
here His power and creation, we'd find that there in verse number 25 that God

247
00:11:15,199 --> 00:11:20,239
is making, He is forming these land-based animals that we're looking at this

248
00:11:20,239 --> 00:11:24,879
evening, and He's forming them from that which had been created earlier on. When

249
00:11:24,879 --> 00:11:30,079
God created earlier on in the first few days of creation, we find that He uses

250
00:11:30,079 --> 00:11:33,679
those elements that were created and now He's making the beast of the earth

251
00:11:33,679 --> 00:11:37,279
after His kind, cattle after their kind, everything that creepeth upon the earth

252
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:41,999
after His kind, and God saw that it was good. And so we first see the declaration

253
00:11:41,999 --> 00:11:46,179
of God. I'm thankful that God's power is revealed through His Word. I'm thankful

254
00:11:46,179 --> 00:11:49,499
